      "symbol": "schema-codec-tests",
      "kind": "schema-policy-advisory",
      "status": "exception",
      "ruleId": "SFV4-arbitrary-tests",
      "line": 7,
      "owner": "@beep/schema",
      "reason": "Exception: CurrencyCode/CurrencyName are LiteralKit unions over the generated ISO 4217 enumeration; example-based assertions cover representative decode/reject and `.Options` membership, and S.toArbitrary over a finite literal union only re-samples already-enumerated members, so schema-derived property coverage would be vacuous."
    },
    {
      "file": "packages/foundation/modeling/schema/test/Fn.test.ts",
      "symbol": "schema-codec-tests",
      "kind": "schema-policy-advisory",
      "status": "exception",
      "ruleId": "SFV4-arbitrary-tests",
      "line": 33,
      "owner": "@beep/schema",
      "reason": "Exception: meta-test of the Fn/ThunkOf/AnyFn schema combinator over function values (declareConstructor with self-identity equivalence); no structural data for S.toArbitrary to generate or round-trip."
    },
    {
      "file": "packages/foundation/modeling/schema/test/MappedLiteralKit.test.ts",
      "symbol": "schema-codec-tests",
      "kind": "schema-policy-advisory",
      "status": "exception",
      "ruleId": "SFV4-arbitrary-tests",
      "line": 13,
      "owner": "@beep/schema",
      "reason": "Exception: meta-test of the MappedLiteralKit combinator using test-local literal pairs; exercises combinator mechanics, not a domain schema law."
    },
    {
      "file": "packages/foundation/modeling/schema/test/PromiseSchema.test.ts",
      "symbol": "schema-codec-tests",
      "kind": "schema-policy-advisory",
      "status": "exception",
      "ruleId": "SFV4-arbitrary-tests",
      "line": 10,
      "owner": "@beep/schema",
      "reason": "Exception: PromiseSchema is a pure S.declare<globalThis.Promise<unknown>> identity declaration (Type === Encoded === a native Promise, no codec transform). S.toArbitrary throws 'Unsupported AST Declaration', and a Promise cannot be meaningfully round-tripped (decode/encode are identity, equivalence is reference equality), so any property law would be vacuous. Cross-realm acceptance and thenable-impostor rejection are covered by example-based unit tests."
    },
    {
      "file": "packages/foundation/modeling/schema/test/TerritoryCode.test.ts",
      "symbol": "schema-codec-tests",
      "kind": "schema-policy-advisory",
      "status": "exception",
      "ruleId": "SFV4-arbitrary-tests",
      "line": 10,
      "owner": "@beep/schema",
      "reason": "Exception: TerritoryCode/TerritoryName and their code<->name MappedLiteralKit codecs are finite literal-union schemas over the generated CLDR enumeration; representative decode/encode and reversible-mapping cases are covered by example assertions, and S.toArbitrary over the finite enumeration adds no coverage beyond the enumerated members."
    },
    {
      "file": "packages/foundation/modeling/schema/test/Timezone.test.ts",
      "symbol": "schema-codec-tests",
